================================================================================
Vulnerability and malware data
================================================================================

Converge queries the OSV.dev API (https://osv.dev) at runtime to detect known
vulnerabilities and malware. No OSV data is bundled with Converge; advisory
records are fetched live and remain (c) their respective sources under their own
licenses, including:

  - GitHub Advisory Database (GHSA)   -- CC-BY-4.0
  - PyPI Advisory Database (PyPA)     -- CC-BY-4.0
  - Go Vulnerability Database         -- CC-BY-4.0
  - RustSec Advisory Database         -- CC0-1.0
  - OpenSSF Malicious Packages        -- Apache-2.0
  - and other sources aggregated by OSV.dev

Each advisory Converge surfaces links back to https://osv.dev/vulnerability/<id>.
For the full source list and licenses, see https://google.github.io/osv.dev/data/.

Converge does not use or bundle osv-scanner; it calls the public OSV.dev HTTP API
directly. The API base is configurable via the CONVERGE_OSV_API environment
variable.
